rows.label: tev032201_JNK0010
rows.name: Inquire[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_SEL0011
rows.name: Ask Rutantan about Ma-non technology.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_JNK0020
rows.name: Discuss[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_SEL0021
rows.name: Ask Rutantan about recent developments.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_SEL0031
rows.name: Ask Rutantan how the Ma-non fared during the attack.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_SEL0041
rows.name: Ask Rutantan about the Ma-non language.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0001
rows.name:
It's no wonder the Ganglion want our technology.
I mean, it's the finest in in in all the universe, right?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0002
rows.name:
...Hmm? What's with that look? Are you wondering
how these silly, lazy Ma-non can be the producers of
the most jaw-dropping breakthroughs in the cosmos?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0003
rows.name:
We aren't fools, are we? We just have to invent
something once, then never worry about it again.
I mean, who works more than they have to?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0004
rows.name: Heck, we invent things BECAUSE we're lazy, you see?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0008
rows.name:
I suppose the Ganglion's tech has its own merits?
One might even call it "advanced."[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0009
rows.name: I'd like to study it if if given the chance...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0010
rows.name:
But all they seem to produce is weapons, right?
And we hate weapons. So I'm not so sure I'll
like what I find, you know?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0016
rows.name:
Lara's boyfriend was killed during the attack,
wasn't he? It's very very sad...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0017
rows.name:
I tried bringing him some yummy sweets and pretty
flowers to to help him feel better, you know?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0018
rows.name:
He told me once that people like to be surprised with
these kinds of things, you see?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0019
rows.name:
Anyway, I had to do something, because I was afraid
all that water coming from his eyes might end up
drowning me, you know?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0020
rows.name:
You humans sure are good at speaking Ma-non,
aren't you?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0021
rows.name:
...What's that? You're NOT speaking Ma-non?
Well, how how odd.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0022
rows.name:
Now that I think about it, how could you you even
pronounce it? Our speech organs are totally different
from yours...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0023
rows.name:
That's a bit...creepy? The understanding, I mean.
How is this even working...?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_SEL1021
rows.name: Ask Rutantan about recent developments.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0011
rows.name:
We need to put our fear of weapons aside, don't
you think? We must start making them so that you
humans can can fight and bring peace to Mira...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0012
rows.name:
The Ma-non do not like to participate in acts of war,
but we are also not fools, you know?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0013
rows.name:
And if we leave the Ganglion to their ways,
I imagine no one will ever be happy...?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0014
rows.name:
I must thank you for teaching us this,
[ST:playername ].[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev032201_MSG0015
rows.name:
And I must thank Lara, too, because if I do not,
I imagine he will likely hug me again?
And he nearly broke my my my bones last time![ST:wait ]
